name: collection-basic
longdesc: These files are regarded as basic for any TeX system, covering plain TeX macros, Computer Modern fonts, and configuration for common drivers; no LaTeX.

name: collection-bibtexextra
longdesc: Additional BibTeX styles and bibliography data(bases), notably including BibLaTeX.

name: collection-binextra
longdesc: Myriad additional TeX-related support programs. Includes programs and macros for DVI file manipulation, literate programming, patgen, and plenty more.
Hans Hagen's powerful ConTeXt system, http://pragma-ade.com. Also includes third-party ConTeXt packages.
name: collection-context

longdesc: Recommended fonts, including the base 35 PostScript fonts, Latin Modern, TeX Gyre, and T1 and other encoding support for Computer Modern, in outline form.
name: collection-fontsrecommended

longdesc: Programs for conversion between font formats, testing fonts, virtual fonts, .gf and .pk manipulation, mft, fontinst, etc. Manipulating OpenType, TrueType, Type 1,and for manipulation of PostScript and other image formats.
name: collection-fontutils

longdesc: Collected TeX `formats', i.e., large-scale macro packages designed to be dumped into .fmt files -- excluding the most common ones, such as latex and context, which have their own package(s). It also includes the Aleph engine and related Omega formats and packages.
name: collection-formatsextra
collection-games
longdesc: Setups for typesetting various games, including chess.
Packages for law, linguistics, social sciences, humanities, etc.
name: collection-humanities
collection-langarabic
longdesc: Support for Arabic and Persian.

name: collection-langchinese
longdesc: Support for Chinese; additional packages in collection-langcjk.

name: collection-langcjk
longdesc: Packages supporting a combination of Chinese, Japanese, Korean, including macros, fonts, documentation. Also Thai in the c90 encoding, since there is some overlap in those fonts; standard Thai support is in collection-langother. Additional packages for CJK are in their individual language collections.

name: collection-langcyrillic
longdesc: Support for Cyrillic scripts (Bulgarian, Russian, Serbian, Ukrainian), even if Latin alphabets may also be used.

name: collection-langczechslovak
longdesc: Support for Czech/Slovak.

name: collection-langenglish
longdesc: Support for, and documentation in, English.
Support for a number of European languages; others (Greek, German, French, ...) have their own collections, depending simply on the size of the support.
name: collection-langeuropean

longdesc: Support for French and Basque.
name: collection-langfrench
collection-langgerman
longdesc: Support for German.
Support for Greek.
name: collection-langgreek

longdesc: Support for Italian.
name: collection-langitalian

longdesc: Support for Japanese; additional packages are in collection-langcjk.
name: collection-langjapanese

longdesc: Support for Korean; additional packages in collection-langcjk.
name: collection-langkorean

longdesc: Support for languages not otherwise listed, including Indic, Thai, Vietnamese, Hebrew, Indonesian, African languages, and plenty more. The split is made simply on the basis of the size of the support, to keep both collection sizes and the number of collections reasonable.
name: collection-langother

longdesc: Support for Polish.
name: collection-langpolish
collection-langportuguese
longdesc: Support for Portuguese.
Support for Spanish.
name: collection-langspanish
collection-latex
longdesc: These packages are either mandated by the core LaTeX team, or very widely used and strongly recommended in practice.

name: collection-latexextra
longdesc: A very large collection of add-on packages for LaTeX.
A collection of recommended add-on packages for LaTeX which have widespread use, and the release candidate formats latex-dev, etc.
name: collection-latexrecommended
collection-luatex
longdesc: Packages for LuaTeX, a Unicode-aware extension of pdfTeX, using Lua as an embedded scripting and extension language. http://luatex.org/

shortdesc: Mathematics, natural sciences, computer science packages
name: collection-mathscience
collection-music
longdesc: Music-related fonts and packages.

name: collection-pictures
longdesc: Including TikZ, pict, etc., but MetaPost and PStricks are separate.
Add-on packages and macros that work with plain TeX, often LaTeX, and occasionally other formats.
name: collection-plaingeneric

longdesc: PSTricks core and all add-on packages.
name: collection-pstricks
collection-texworks
longdesc: See http://tug.org/texworks.
shortdesc: TeXworks editor; TL includes only the Windows binary

longdesc: Utilities for Windows, since they are not readily available there: chktex, unzip, wget, xpdf, and the dviout previewer.
name: collection-wintools

longdesc: Packages for XeTeX, the Unicode/OpenType-enabled TeX by Jonathan Kew, http://tug.org/xetex.
name: collection-xetex
